quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  93,1,BY the noon-day BRIGHTNESS
  93,2,And by the night when it darkeneth
  93,3,"Thy Lord hath not forsaken thee, neither hath he been displeased"
  93,4,And surely the Future shall be better for thee than the Past
  93,5,And in the end shall thy Lord be bounteous to thee and thou be satisfied
  93,6,Did he not find thee an orphan and gave thee a home
  93,7,And found thee erring and guided thee
  93,8,And found thee needy and enriched thee
  93,9,As to the orphan therefore wrong him not
  93,10,"And as to him that asketh of thee, chide him not away"
  93,11,And as for the favours of thy Lord tell them abroad